https://nikitahl.com/style-range-input-css

 <script>
    <!-- This Script controls the slider selector for the filter section-->
    const value = document.querySelector("#value")
    const input = document.querySelector("#slider")
    value.textContent = input.value
    input.addEventListener("input", (event) => {
    value.textContent = event.target.value
    })
 </script>
 
 This script works to get to show the value of the script on an specific span using the #value for the id of the span or any label and #slider for the slider id
 here's an example bellow 
 
 <span> Grade, over: <strong><output id="value"></output> g/t</strong></span>
 <input id="slider" type="range" min="0" max="100" value="31" />
